<p>
<p>Bob is interested in the effect of feedback on fathers’ comforting of crying babies (two conditions: positive or negative feedback) on fathers’ levels of self-confidence (self-report based on 30 questions). In doing so, he intends to statistically control for the number of years of experience of fatherhood (in months).</p>
<p>What analysis technique should Bob use?</p>
</p>]]></text>
</questiontext>
<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
<penalty>0</penalty>
<defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
<shuffleanswers>false</shuffleanswers>
<single>true</single>
<answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Simple linear regression analysis
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Multiple logistic regression analysis
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Two-way analysis of variance (‘Two-way ANOVA’)
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="100" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Covariance analysis (ANCOVA)
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Correct
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
